1 00:00:07.600 --> 00:00:10.680a booking chart is linked to any OpenERP model2 00:00:10.680 --> 00:00:13.840this model is used for the booking chart rows3 00:00:16.800 --> 00:00:20.000a resource booking is a period item displayed in the booking chart4 00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:23.520the resource id make the link with the booking chart5 00:00:23.520 --> 00:00:26.600origins are used to link the resource with any OpenERP object6 00:00:31.240 --> 00:00:33.960the native OpenERP search widget is used to filter / group booking chart resources7 00:00:34.680 --> 00:00:37.760when resources booking are overlapping, they are grouped8 00:00:38.480 --> 00:00:41.760different dynamic zoom levels are available9 00:00:55.640 --> 00:00:59.080the period navigation is made with an horizontal scrollbar10 00:00:59.080 --> 00:01:02.000when the scrollbar reach one extremity, the next / previous month is loaded dynamically11 00:01:02.000 --> 00:01:05.080and resources booking are lazy loaded12 00:01:18.160 --> 00:01:21.400a click on a resource booking give access to his origin object13 00:01:26.040 --> 00:01:29.160a click on a booking chart resource will display it14 00:01:34.000 --> 00:01:37.000the native group feature is available15 00:01:45.600 --> 00:01:48.920the calendar period is manually selectable16 00:01:54.400 --> 00:01:57.440by default, the navigation is frozen after a manual period selection17 00:02:02.520 --> 00:02:05.640the navigation can be frozen / unfrozen with a button18 00:02:26.360 --> 00:02:29.480a pagination is also available on booking chart resources